===Etymology===
*A translation of the original [[Min Nan]] term: [[зёӣ]][[жҹұд»”и…і]] ([[POJ]]: paМҚk thiДҒu-ГЎ-kha, literally: to tie the base of the piles together).  The Mandarin equivalent of [[зёӣ]] ([[POJ]]: paМҚk, English: to tie, to bind together) is [[з¶Ғ]], and the Mandarin equivalent of [[жҹұд»”]] ([[POJ]]: thiДҒu-ГЎ, English: stake, pile, post) is [[жЁҒ]].  The phrase "to tie together one's base piles" is a metaphor for when a politician earmarks money in a budget in order to benefit key supporters (such as local political leaders, companies with government contracts etc) in return for their political support, either in the form of campaign contributions or votes.

